THE National Assembly on Thursday suspended Arusha Urban Member of Parliament (MP) GodblessLema under Chadema ticket from attending three parliamentary meetings following his affirmation statements that the Parliament is weak. Members of the Assembly passed such verdict against the opposition lawmaker after unanimously endorsing a resolution presented in the House by the Parliamentary Privileges, Ethics and Powers, which found him guilty of the offence he was charged with. According to the Committee Chairperson Emmanuel Mwakasaka, the Parliament affirmed and agreed to approve the recommendations of the penalty against Mr Lema as the committee proposed. â€œTherefore, the Parliament resolves that Mr Lema be suspended from attending three parliamentary meetings from the date of this resolution," the Committee Chairman, Mr Emmanuel Mwakasaka, declared.